Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:15:13.843 --> 01:15:15.678
[audience cheers louder]

01:15:24.938 --> 01:15:25.855
A very impressive entrance.

01:15:25.980 --> 01:15:27.482
I think in the 10 years
we've been doing this show,

01:15:27.607 --> 01:15:30.443
I've never seen anything
quite like that.

01:15:30.568 --> 01:15:31.929
- I want to do
what the king wants,

01:15:32.028 --> 01:15:33.530
so I'd like to do that.

01:15:35.532 --> 01:15:38.409
I'm on the Dave Letterman show!
By golly...

01:15:38.535 --> 01:15:39.452
- How are you doing, buddy?

01:15:39.577 --> 01:15:41.287
All excited
about your big movie?

01:15:41.412 --> 01:15:42.693
- Aw, man.
- You and David Spade.

01:15:42.747 --> 01:15:44.707
David Spade, a very funny man,
very nice guy,

01:15:44.832 --> 01:15:46.334
and you guys are friends

01:15:46.459 --> 01:15:47.794
as well as working together
on the show,

01:15:47.919 --> 01:15:49.420
and now on this big movie.

01:15:49.546 --> 01:15:51.506
- Yeah, he's my buddy.
We had a lot of fun.

01:15:51.631 --> 01:15:54.717
- When the movie came out,
the reviews were bad.

01:15:54.842 --> 01:15:58.846
For him, the idea that it could
be that willfully hurtful

01:15:59.389 --> 01:16:00.431
took him back,

01:16:01.766 --> 01:16:02.767
and he didn't have
the confidence yet,

01:16:02.892 --> 01:16:04.686
because it was his first movie,
you know,

01:16:04.811 --> 01:16:07.355
because I'd say,
"Let them wash over you,"

01:16:07.480 --> 01:16:09.107
"and in two weeks,
nobody will care."

01:16:09.232 --> 01:16:10.525
"All that matters is the work,"

01:16:10.650 --> 01:16:13.820
"and it's a piece of work
that will be around."

01:16:14.904 --> 01:16:17.031
- When the video came out,
it was an obsession.

01:16:17.156 --> 01:16:21.786
Our generation was into him,
and that was the coolest.

01:16:23.121 --> 01:16:26.040
- It's interesting that a movie
that was that savaged

01:16:26.165 --> 01:16:29.919
ended up being sort of a movie
that's never gone away.

01:16:30.420 --> 01:16:34.841
- Time magazine published a page
of the 10 Comedies of All Time,

01:16:36.092 --> 01:16:37.677
and Tommy Boy's there,

01:16:38.720 --> 01:16:41.681
and I know that Farley
would have been incredibly proud

01:16:41.806 --> 01:16:42.890
to see it there.

01:16:43.141 --> 01:16:44.434
- I really love this movie.

01:16:44.559 --> 01:16:45.560
I hope
that everyone will like it,

01:16:45.685 --> 01:16:47.145
because we had fun making it,
and I think it's really good.

01:16:47.270 --> 01:16:48.354
- I hope so, too.

01:16:48.646 --> 01:16:49.897
I hope it's a huge hit for you
and for David Spade

01:16:50.023 --> 01:16:51.357
and everybody else as well.

01:16:51.482 --> 01:16:52.483
- Because if I don't,

01:16:52.609 --> 01:16:53.985
I'm going back
to Wisconsin on the farm,

01:16:54.110 --> 01:16:55.153
so go to it!

01:16:55.612 --> 01:16:56.988
No, no, that was stupid too.

01:16:57.113 --> 01:16:58.156
I shouldn't have...

01:16:58.281 --> 01:16:59.281
- [laughs]

01:16:59.365 --> 01:17:00.617
- Chris was at a place,

01:17:00.742 --> 01:17:02.702
not that he didn't need
SNL at that point,

01:17:02.827 --> 01:17:03.827
because it feels

01:17:03.828 --> 01:17:05.622
like it just had kind of
run its course.

01:17:05.747 --> 01:17:06.748
- Once you're on the show

01:17:06.873 --> 01:17:09.626
and then you're in a movie
that does really, really well,

01:17:09.751 --> 01:17:11.753
it's weird being on the show.

01:17:13.838 --> 01:17:15.958
It's not like you think
you're better than the show...

01:17:15.965 --> 01:17:17.216
never, of course.

01:17:17.759 --> 01:17:19.677
The movies are a lot of work.

01:17:19.844 --> 01:17:22.430
The love you get
for what you've done

01:17:22.764 --> 01:17:23.931
lasts for years,

01:17:24.265 --> 01:17:26.466
and on Saturday Night Live,
it's gone by Sunday morning.

01:17:26.476 --> 01:17:27.518
- For Chris,

01:17:27.810 --> 01:17:30.813
the pull of Hollywood
was now very strong.

01:17:31.397 --> 01:17:33.983
A new administration
came in at NBC.

01:17:34.442 --> 01:17:36.444
I think they did not like him.

01:17:36.736 --> 01:17:38.905
They did not like Adam Sandler.

01:17:39.113 --> 01:17:43.076
It was a generational change.

01:17:44.744 --> 01:17:47.205
- What happens
after SNL is scary, man,

01:17:47.330 --> 01:17:49.082
and you don't want it to end.

01:17:49.207 --> 01:17:50.708
I remember the last party,

01:17:50.833 --> 01:17:52.502
looking at each other
and being like,

01:17:52.627 --> 01:17:55.880
"This is it, man?
This is over, that great run?

01:17:56.339 --> 01:17:57.382
Now what?"

01:17:57.799 --> 01:17:58.758
- From my own experience
being on the show,

01:17:58.883 --> 01:18:00.635
you always wanted,
like, to be on the show

01:18:00.760 --> 01:18:03.179
and then have a movie out
that was a hit

01:18:03.304 --> 01:18:04.305
at the same time,

01:18:04.430 --> 01:18:06.140
and so if they don't do well,

01:18:06.265 --> 01:18:07.725
you think, "Well, at least
I still have the show,"

01:18:07.850 --> 01:18:09.560
"so I'm not, like,
completely out of it."

01:18:09.686 --> 01:18:12.605
- And he was getting big offers
to do stuff,

01:18:12.730 --> 01:18:14.774
big money,
they had big directors,

01:18:14.899 --> 01:18:16.192
everybody loved him.

01:18:16.317 --> 01:18:17.735
So he had stuff to do,

01:18:18.277 --> 01:18:21.614
but there's that fear of,
like, "What the hell am I doing?"

01:18:21.739 --> 01:18:23.574
"Why am I going
to be out on my own?"

01:18:23.700 --> 01:18:24.617
because there,
you're a team together,

01:18:24.742 --> 01:18:27.161
then all of a sudden,
it's all you.

01:18:28.121 --> 01:18:29.622
- He said, "Kitten..."

01:18:30.123 --> 01:18:32.291
"I only saw myself
doing Saturday Night Live."

01:18:32.417 --> 01:18:35.169
"Like, that was my goal,
was to do Saturday Night Live"

01:18:35.294 --> 01:18:37.046
"and make my father laugh."

01:18:37.380 --> 01:18:39.882
"I never imagined myself
doing movies."

01:18:40.007 --> 01:18:41.509
And I said, "Oh, no..."

01:18:42.552 --> 01:18:44.345
"It's not in his comfort zone,"

01:18:44.470 --> 01:18:46.305
and when
you don't get in your...

01:18:46.431 --> 01:18:47.765
you're past your comfort zone,

01:18:47.890 --> 01:18:49.767
you've got to make sure
you're really grounded.

01:18:49.892 --> 01:18:52.729
Otherwise,
it can just be overwhelming.

01:18:55.940 --> 01:18:57.483
- He was a giant TV star,
a giant movie star,

01:18:57.608 --> 01:18:59.193
but the kind of routine

01:18:59.652 --> 01:19:00.932
of having the show
and the family

01:19:01.028 --> 01:19:03.656
and the same people and Lorne
and all his "brothers,"

01:19:03.781 --> 01:19:06.200
and without that,
it wasn't the same.

01:19:06.325 --> 01:19:07.368
I mean,

01:19:07.869 --> 01:19:09.909
it might have made him feel
like he was floundering,

01:19:09.912 --> 01:19:12.165
like there wasn't the safety
of the show,

01:19:12.290 --> 01:19:15.877
the security of that set...
family atmosphere.

01:19:21.924 --> 01:19:23.176
- Hi, ma'am.

01:19:25.136 --> 01:19:25.970
Vote for Donnelly.

01:19:26.095 --> 01:19:28.097
- Tommy Boy's a movie
that stayed with people,

01:19:28.222 --> 01:19:29.974
and then what happens
is the studio is sort of like,

01:19:30.099 --> 01:19:31.851
"We're going to try
to replicate that."

01:19:31.976 --> 01:19:33.686
"We're going to try
to grab whatever Tommy Boy had"

01:19:33.811 --> 01:19:35.646
"and make it that again,"
you know,

01:19:35.772 --> 01:19:36.773
and I get that.

01:19:36.898 --> 01:19:39.650
- Paramount had an option on him
from Tommy Boy,

01:19:39.776 --> 01:19:40.818
and so he had to do Black Sheep.

01:19:40.943 --> 01:19:43.529
- Fred Wolf was 60 pages
into the script

01:19:43.654 --> 01:19:44.739
when we were green-lit,

01:19:44.864 --> 01:19:45.865
and I went,

01:19:45.990 --> 01:19:47.470
"We don't actually
have a script yet."

01:19:47.533 --> 01:19:48.694
- Listen, I think it's better

01:19:48.743 --> 01:19:50.161
if we bring the energy
down a tad.

01:19:50.286 --> 01:19:51.496
- Are you kidding me?

01:19:51.621 --> 01:19:52.621
It's showmanship.

01:19:52.705 --> 01:19:53.539
You've got to go out
and get 'em.

01:19:53.664 --> 01:19:54.664
- It was like Tommy Boy.

01:19:54.707 --> 01:19:55.541
We wanted to get back
and do that.

01:19:55.666 --> 01:19:56.501
He goes,
"That's the one people like,

01:19:56.626 --> 01:19:57.752
and we should try it again."

01:19:57.877 --> 01:19:59.754
Fred gave him
a rolling down a hill.

01:19:59.879 --> 01:20:01.506
He'd just keep falling,
because it gets funnier

01:20:01.631 --> 01:20:02.882
because it's so stupid.

01:20:03.007 --> 01:20:04.801
He's just very good at anything
you give him like that.

01:20:04.926 --> 01:20:08.721
He can come up with, like,
jerky moves and funny faces,

01:20:08.846 --> 01:20:10.765
and he snaps his head around.

01:20:11.599 --> 01:20:12.642
- Bunk beds.

01:20:13.643 --> 01:20:15.061
I've got dibs on top.

01:20:15.269 --> 01:20:16.312
- Okay.

01:20:16.479 --> 01:20:17.519
- In the cabin with David,

01:20:17.522 --> 01:20:19.774
or him
rolling down that hill, <i>or...</i>

01:20:19.899 --> 01:20:22.318
There was
lots of really funny things.

01:20:22.443 --> 01:20:23.736
- Nothing's going
to stop us now.

01:20:23.861 --> 01:20:24.695
[engine fails to start]

01:20:24.821 --> 01:20:25.738
- We knew there was a difference

01:20:25.863 --> 01:20:26.906
between Black Sheep
and Tommy Boy,

01:20:27.031 --> 01:20:28.574
and Chris knew that, too.

01:20:28.699 --> 01:20:29.742
The process became interrupted.

01:20:29.867 --> 01:20:33.621
It just got to be manipulated
by people from outside.

01:20:34.038 --> 01:20:36.123
- Okay,
maybe we could use some help.

01:20:36.249 --> 01:20:37.083
- The two pictures grossed

01:20:37.208 --> 01:20:39.126
almost exactly
the same amount of money,

01:20:39.252 --> 01:20:42.755
so the fact that one vehicle
maybe was a little rushed

01:20:42.880 --> 01:20:46.467
and maybe not made as lovingly
as the first one was,

01:20:46.926 --> 01:20:49.136
that's what you take away
when you're doing it.

01:20:49.262 --> 01:20:50.382
- Chris was a perfectionist,

01:20:50.388 --> 01:20:54.225
and he was always, you know,
he just wanted to do the best,

01:20:54.350 --> 01:20:56.591
and if it wasn't the best,
he was really hard on himself.

01:20:56.644 --> 01:20:58.479
- Just because
things aren't perfect

01:20:58.604 --> 01:21:00.898
doesn't mean
people won't like them.

01:21:01.023 --> 01:21:04.026
- Unfortunately,
I was with him when it...

01:21:05.319 --> 01:21:06.362
when it...

01:21:06.904 --> 01:21:08.364
when he relapsed the first time.

01:21:08.489 --> 01:21:09.532
And we were...

01:21:11.158 --> 01:21:12.660
He called me up, and he said,
"Do you want to go see...

01:21:12.785 --> 01:21:15.872
We're doing a preview show
of Black Sheep."

01:21:16.956 --> 01:21:18.958
He was just getting nervous,
and he was upset,

01:21:19.083 --> 01:21:21.711
and to see it onscreen,
he was like...

01:21:21.836 --> 01:21:23.963
it just was enough
to set him off.

01:21:24.088 --> 01:21:25.528
And the next day,
my Dad calls me up.

01:21:25.631 --> 01:21:27.675
He was like,
"What happened last night?"

01:21:27.800 --> 01:21:29.000
It's like, "What do you mean?"

01:21:29.051 --> 01:21:30.932
It's like, "Christopher
trashed his hotel room,"

01:21:30.970 --> 01:21:34.724
"and, you know, he's back
in the, you know, rehab, and..."

01:21:34.849 --> 01:21:35.850
It's like, holy shit.

01:21:35.975 --> 01:21:38.603
- So he went off the handle
for two weeks,

01:21:38.728 --> 01:21:40.730
then they dragged him
back into rehab.

01:21:40.855 --> 01:21:41.939
A couple more rehabs,

01:21:42.064 --> 01:21:44.901
and then sober
for Beverly Hills Ninja.

01:21:45.693 --> 01:21:46.903
- Here's the thing.

01:21:47.028 --> 01:21:48.349
If you're a drug addict,
you know,

01:21:48.446 --> 01:21:49.697
and an alcoholic,

01:21:49.864 --> 01:21:51.282
all of a sudden you're sober,
you're sober today.

01:21:51.407 --> 01:21:52.575
Like, it's a day.

01:21:52.700 --> 01:21:53.784
"I'm sober.
Oh, look at me, I'm sober."

01:21:53.910 --> 01:21:56.787
But if you're fat,
and I speak from experience...

01:21:56.913 --> 01:21:57.914
you look in the mirror,

01:21:58.039 --> 01:21:59.332
and you've eaten healthy
one day,

01:21:59.457 --> 01:22:00.708
you're still fat.

01:22:00.875 --> 01:22:02.877
You're like,
"How do I beat this thing?"

01:22:03.002 --> 01:22:03.961
- I have always looked up to you,

01:22:04.086 --> 01:22:05.922
and you have always
looked out for me,

01:22:06.047 --> 01:22:07.847
but now it is time
that I look out for myself.

01:22:07.965 --> 01:22:09.717
- Be careful in your travels,
Haru.

01:22:09.842 --> 01:22:11.594
The world is a dangerous place.

01:22:11.719 --> 01:22:12.929
[grunts]

01:22:14.013 --> 01:22:15.573
- When I saw him,
and he was cleaned up,

01:22:15.681 --> 01:22:16.849
and he'd been to rehab
a couple times,

01:22:16.974 --> 01:22:19.810
and he was refusing booze
at this party,

01:22:20.061 --> 01:22:22.229
he was standing up for himself,

01:22:23.022 --> 01:22:25.062
and he wasn't a kid going,
"What? What do you want?"

01:22:25.149 --> 01:22:27.902
"Oh, yeah, cool, great,
whatever you've got I'll do"

01:22:28.027 --> 01:22:30.780
"to make you happy,
to be a part of this."

01:22:31.364 --> 01:22:34.200
He was saying,
"No, I need to protect myself."

01:22:34.325 --> 01:22:37.912
- I think it's important
to just have a self-esteem

01:22:38.955 --> 01:22:40.623
and believe in yourself

01:22:41.123 --> 01:22:43.376
and be able to tell the world...

01:22:46.045 --> 01:22:48.965
I guess, "Go fuck yourself,"
on some level.

01:22:51.550 --> 01:22:53.970
It's a tough thing to deal with
that kind of fame

01:22:54.095 --> 01:22:54.929
when you're that fam...

01:22:55.054 --> 01:22:58.057
And if it happens fast,
it's almost lethal

01:22:59.058 --> 01:23:00.810
if you don't really have
a firm belief

01:23:00.935 --> 01:23:02.478
in what you are
and what you're doing.

01:23:02.603 --> 01:23:03.938
- It's sad to me, though,

01:23:04.063 --> 01:23:05.982
that he didn't love himself

01:23:06.440 --> 01:23:08.275
as much as everybody around him
loved him.

01:23:08.401 --> 01:23:12.571
- He went through 17 rehabs,
but he was a committed athlete.

01:23:13.072 --> 01:23:16.409
He was not going
to let this addiction beat him.

01:23:16.951 --> 01:23:17.952
- I would love

01:23:18.077 --> 01:23:20.204
when he'd come back
from any rehab

01:23:20.329 --> 01:23:21.998
and be fresh and be like,

01:23:22.873 --> 01:23:24.375
"I'm done with that,"

01:23:24.625 --> 01:23:27.211
and he had his eating
under control,

01:23:27.586 --> 01:23:28.921
and he was excited.

01:23:29.130 --> 01:23:31.716
He was excited
to have that new shot.

01:23:32.133 --> 01:23:35.553
- Chris sober was the most
brilliant, brightest thing

01:23:35.678 --> 01:23:37.013
I'd ever seen in my life.

01:23:37.138 --> 01:23:38.097
To this day,
nothing's come close.

01:23:38.222 --> 01:23:40.683
- You can't walk around
being funny all the time.

01:23:40.808 --> 01:23:42.129
You have to be yourself
sometimes,

01:23:42.226 --> 01:23:44.020
and you have to be alone
sometimes.

01:23:44.145 --> 01:23:46.022
You can't be on stage
all the time.

01:23:46.147 --> 01:23:48.816
- I think when Fatty falls down,
everybody goes home happy.

01:23:48.941 --> 01:23:50.860
It's easier than dialogue.

01:23:51.110 --> 01:23:52.778
I don't have much brain.

01:23:53.237 --> 01:23:56.032
- But Chris also had
such a terrible self-image.

01:23:56.157 --> 01:23:57.491
"Fatty fall down,"

01:23:58.200 --> 01:23:59.869
and "I'm just an idiot."

01:24:00.077 --> 01:24:02.078
And everyone around him
would go, "No, you're not."

01:24:02.079 --> 01:24:04.832
"You're really smart,
and you're a great person,"

01:24:04.957 --> 01:24:06.375
and he'd go, "No, I'm not."

01:24:06.500 --> 01:24:07.334
- There's you, there's...

01:24:07.460 --> 01:24:08.502
[Crash]

01:24:09.003 --> 01:24:10.254
Whoops-a-daisy.

01:24:10.796 --> 01:24:12.548
By god, whoops-a-daisy.

01:24:13.049 --> 01:24:17.011
- It's interesting when people
put out an image of themself

01:24:17.136 --> 01:24:20.139
and then in some way
have to live that life.

01:24:22.266 --> 01:24:24.143
People want that, expect that,

01:24:24.268 --> 01:24:26.687
and if you don't get
to go offstage

01:24:27.271 --> 01:24:29.440
and somehow restore yourself,

01:24:30.024 --> 01:24:31.358
the pull of it <i>is...</i>

01:24:33.110 --> 01:24:34.528
you know, the flame,

01:24:35.029 --> 01:24:37.240
and you can get burned
to a crisp.

01:24:37.364 --> 01:24:38.885
- And now,
here with another commentary

01:24:38.991 --> 01:24:40.431
is Update commentator
Bennett Brauer.

01:24:40.534 --> 01:24:41.534
Bennett?

01:24:41.577 --> 01:24:43.245
[applause]

01:24:46.999 --> 01:24:48.417
- He had a big appetite...

01:24:48.542 --> 01:24:49.919
a big appetite for life,

01:24:50.044 --> 01:24:51.462
for food, for drink,

01:24:51.879 --> 01:24:53.047
for late nights,

01:24:54.131 --> 01:24:56.092
for the pleasures of the earth.

01:24:56.217 --> 01:24:58.469
- Well, maybe I'm not "the norm."

01:24:59.762 --> 01:25:01.764
I'm not "camera-friendly."

01:25:02.306 --> 01:25:04.809
I don't "wear clothes
that fit me."

01:25:05.101 --> 01:25:07.019
- You know, he sincerely wanted
to be sober,

01:25:07.144 --> 01:25:09.563
and was sober
for periods of time,

01:25:09.730 --> 01:25:10.773
and...

01:25:11.065 --> 01:25:12.775
but I always said,
"You can't be fat, super-fat,"

01:25:12.900 --> 01:25:14.151
"and a drug addict."

01:25:14.276 --> 01:25:15.319
"You've got to pick one."

01:25:15.444 --> 01:25:18.781
- I'm not "hygienic."
I don't "wipe properly."

01:25:19.240 --> 01:25:20.324
I lack "style."

01:25:20.991 --> 01:25:23.828
I have no "charisma"
or "self-esteem."

01:25:25.287 --> 01:25:27.456
- Something was, was... amiss.

01:25:28.624 --> 01:25:30.126
Something wasn't working.

01:25:30.251 --> 01:25:31.752
- You know, everyone's going
to do what they're going to do.

01:25:31.877 --> 01:25:32.878
That's the problem.

01:25:33.003 --> 01:25:34.672
There's only so much you can do.

01:25:34.797 --> 01:25:35.756
- I mean,
I'll be honest with you.

01:25:35.881 --> 01:25:36.799
There was something going on
in college.

01:25:36.924 --> 01:25:38.551
That shit
doesn't just creep up on you.

01:25:38.676 --> 01:25:40.177
I mean, I guess
it does creep up on you, but...

01:25:40.302 --> 01:25:42.012
- Alcohol probably being
his first love,

01:25:42.138 --> 01:25:43.973
but he wasn't, you know...

01:25:44.306 --> 01:25:46.267
the other stuff
wasn't far behind.

01:25:48.144 --> 01:25:50.646
- You know,
an addictive person...

01:25:52.648 --> 01:25:54.400
I mean, it's a conundrum.

01:25:54.900 --> 01:25:56.819
- I don't "own a toothbrush"

01:25:57.361 --> 01:25:58.946
or "let my scabs heal."

01:26:00.531 --> 01:26:03.367
I can't "reach
all the parts of my body."

01:26:04.285 --> 01:26:05.285
[audience laughs]

01:26:05.369 --> 01:26:07.788
- There was something
about him that...

01:26:07.913 --> 01:26:09.290
He was just...
I don't know.

01:26:09.415 --> 01:26:11.750
He was in deep,
a hard place to be.

01:26:12.168 --> 01:26:14.003
All of us knew, every time.

01:26:14.295 --> 01:26:16.338
His hair looked different.
He looked sweaty.

01:26:16.463 --> 01:26:18.549
He looked...
His eyes were different.

01:26:18.674 --> 01:26:19.925
They were just...

01:26:20.259 --> 01:26:22.094
You were like, "Oh, shit."

01:26:23.304 --> 01:26:25.055
It was rough seeing him
like that,

01:26:25.181 --> 01:26:26.223
and I hated it.

01:26:26.807 --> 01:26:28.017
- Thank you, Kevin.

01:26:28.142 --> 01:26:29.351
- Bennett Brauer,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:26:29.476 --> 01:26:31.145
- Thank you.

01:26:34.190 --> 01:26:35.733
- I knew he was in trouble.

01:26:35.858 --> 01:26:37.193
People would call me,

01:26:37.318 --> 01:26:39.862
and I thought
the thing he loved the most

01:26:39.987 --> 01:26:41.155
was doing the show.

01:26:41.280 --> 01:26:43.949
He never found the thing
that was as powerful.

01:26:44.074 --> 01:26:45.117
[laughter]

01:26:45.284 --> 01:26:47.036
- Timmy, come back.
Come back. Come back.

01:26:47.161 --> 01:26:49.288
I mean,
I'm not the host tonight,

01:26:49.413 --> 01:26:51.790
and Timmy damn sure
ain't the host tonight.

01:26:51.916 --> 01:26:52.958
[laughing]

01:26:53.751 --> 01:26:55.127
No, the host tonight

01:26:55.252 --> 01:26:57.588
is our good friend,
Chris Farley.

01:26:57.713 --> 01:26:58.713
Come on, Chris.

01:26:58.797 --> 01:26:59.840
[applause]

01:27:00.007 --> 01:27:01.050
- Here we go!

01:27:01.217 --> 01:27:03.010
- Let's do it!
- Let's do it!

01:27:03.135 --> 01:27:04.261
- Whatever shape he was in,

01:27:04.386 --> 01:27:06.513
coming back
and making him go through it

01:27:06.639 --> 01:27:08.265
to realize, if nothing else,

01:27:08.390 --> 01:27:10.100
this is what's happened to you,
you know...

01:27:10.226 --> 01:27:12.061
that thing you're losing,

01:27:12.394 --> 01:27:15.272
that ability to be able
to still play the game,

01:27:15.397 --> 01:27:16.857
which you were an all-star at.

01:27:16.982 --> 01:27:18.275
- You know what I've learned?

01:27:18.400 --> 01:27:20.611
I've learned lessons
about responsibee...

01:27:20.736 --> 01:27:21.987
Responsibility.

01:27:22.446 --> 01:27:25.115
Being responsible,
not only to myself,

01:27:25.241 --> 01:27:26.617
but to the people around me.

01:27:26.742 --> 01:27:28.160
That means you guys.

01:27:28.410 --> 01:27:30.454
I think it's time
to quit goofing around.

01:27:30.579 --> 01:27:32.539
I think it's time
to grow up, fellas.

01:27:32.665 --> 01:27:33.999
I want you...
everything's going to be okay.

01:27:34.124 --> 01:27:35.334
- All right, man.
- Okay.

01:27:35.459 --> 01:27:37.378
- I'm a new Chris, okay, fellas?

01:27:37.503 --> 01:27:40.297
Now, stay,
we've got a great show tonight.

01:27:40.422 --> 01:27:42.758
Mighty Mighty Bosstones
are here,

01:27:42.883 --> 01:27:44.051
so stick around.

01:27:45.135 --> 01:27:48.264
- It's just rare
that a person has that much joy

01:27:48.389 --> 01:27:51.767
and brings that much happiness
to everyone around them,

01:27:51.892 --> 01:27:53.143
but with Chris...

01:27:54.311 --> 01:27:57.398
there's a limit
to how wonderful it is to me.

01:27:59.650 --> 01:28:00.650
And that limit

01:28:00.651 --> 01:28:04.154
is when you kill yourself
with drugs and alcohol.

01:28:04.571 --> 01:28:05.614
You know?

01:28:05.823 --> 01:28:09.285
That's where it stops
being so fucking magical.

01:28:11.453 --> 01:28:13.372
- Things are getting better
and better for you, aren't they?

01:28:13.497 --> 01:28:14.540
- Yeah.

01:28:14.915 --> 01:28:15.958
<i>I...</i> I <i>love it.</i>

01:28:17.334 --> 01:28:19.169
- Success in show business

01:28:19.336 --> 01:28:22.798
does not always create
the best version of people.

01:28:22.923 --> 01:28:25.134
- Do you get a sense now
of how your life might change

01:28:25.259 --> 01:28:26.760
with the fame
that is going to come

01:28:26.885 --> 01:28:28.086
with the release of this film?

01:28:28.178 --> 01:28:29.513
Not that you're not famous now,

01:28:29.638 --> 01:28:31.515
but, you know,
it's going to be more and more.

01:28:31.640 --> 01:28:32.640
- And also thinking

01:28:32.683 --> 01:28:34.643
that you have the physical
capacity to handle it,

01:28:34.768 --> 01:28:36.603
because, you know, you may think
that you can handle it.

01:28:36.729 --> 01:28:38.230
- It's not going to change me.
Going to be the same old Chris.

01:28:38.355 --> 01:28:39.690
- Yeah.
- Nothing's going to happen...

01:28:39.815 --> 01:28:40.815
-om

01:28:40.899 --> 01:28:42.026
- Are you going to be okay?

01:28:42.151 --> 01:28:43.819
- Yeah, I thought that...

01:28:55.539 --> 01:28:58.334
- Maybe this was the life
that he was supposed to live.

01:28:58.459 --> 01:29:00.711
I mean, I'm selfish.
I wanted more.

01:29:00.836 --> 01:29:03.422
- You don't really believe it
when you're going through it.

01:29:03.547 --> 01:29:04.798
You just think...

01:29:05.424 --> 01:29:07.384
that he'd be able
to pull it out.

01:29:07.509 --> 01:29:09.270
- "You're going to die
from that shit, buddy."

01:29:09.303 --> 01:29:11.013
"You've got to stop,
you've got to stop,"

01:29:11.138 --> 01:29:13.098
"and it's just not going
to end right,"

01:29:13.223 --> 01:29:14.475
and then... it...

01:29:16.560 --> 01:29:17.394
[static]

01:29:17.519 --> 01:29:19.605
- The entertainment world
has lost a huge talent,

01:29:19.730 --> 01:29:20.981
and much too soon.

01:29:21.273 --> 01:29:24.360
Comedian Chris Farley
died today in Chicago.

01:29:32.242 --> 01:29:33.577
- I wasn't shocked.

01:29:34.536 --> 01:29:37.206
And I was very sad,
and straight <i>up...</i>

01:29:38.791 --> 01:29:39.833
[sighs]

01:29:40.501 --> 01:29:43.128
Lots of things you wish
didn't happen, you know?

01:29:43.253 --> 01:29:45.005
- You know, he died alone,

01:29:46.882 --> 01:29:48.467
you know, on a linoleum floor.

01:29:48.592 --> 01:29:50.761
It was
not what we wanted for him,

01:29:50.886 --> 01:29:53.055
nor what he wanted for himself.

01:29:53.889 --> 01:29:55.057
- Nobody died...

01:29:55.641 --> 01:29:57.059
You know, you're 33.

01:29:57.476 --> 01:29:58.811
You don't die at 33.

01:29:58.936 --> 01:30:00.270
It doesn't happen.

01:30:00.521 --> 01:30:02.022
- It took months to go,

01:30:02.689 --> 01:30:04.900
"Okay, I can talk about this,
or I could just..."

01:30:05.025 --> 01:30:06.068
Too much.

01:30:06.485 --> 01:30:09.279
It comes up in something
in my mind every day,

01:30:09.405 --> 01:30:11.323
and I think it will forever.

01:30:11.657 --> 01:30:13.742
- I liked having him in my life.
It was better.

01:30:13.867 --> 01:30:16.495
It made my life better
being a friend of mine.

01:30:22.709 --> 01:30:24.169
- Do I wish
I could clone that guy?

01:30:24.294 --> 01:30:25.575
But with Chris,
you just don't...

01:30:25.629 --> 01:30:27.089
When they say,
"God made the mold"

01:30:27.214 --> 01:30:28.535
"and he threw it out the window,"

01:30:28.632 --> 01:30:29.800
there was no mold.

01:30:29.925 --> 01:30:31.176
There was just...

01:30:31.510 --> 01:30:33.387
It was just ether, stars,
comets,

01:30:33.512 --> 01:30:35.514
precious jewels and gems...

01:30:35.806 --> 01:30:37.683
and Chris.

01:30:40.394 --> 01:30:42.020
- Thank you, folks.
You guys have been great.

01:30:42.146 --> 01:30:43.480
Thank you for coming out.

01:30:43.605 --> 01:30:46.150
- Keep it going for Kevin Farley,
everybody.

01:30:46.275 --> 01:30:47.317
[cheering]

01:30:47.651 --> 01:30:49.403
- Chris, he would never want
to bring any sadness.

01:30:49.528 --> 01:30:51.488
What he would want
is just everybody to laugh

01:30:51.613 --> 01:30:52.781
and don't be sad.

01:30:53.574 --> 01:30:55.325
Keep the laughter going.

01:30:55.451 --> 01:30:57.369
- It's called a clown's prayer.

01:30:57.494 --> 01:30:58.815
Before any audition
at Second City

01:30:58.829 --> 01:30:59.997
or for TV or film,

01:31:00.497 --> 01:31:02.458
we'd always take out the prayer.

01:31:02.583 --> 01:31:03.625
We'd read it.

01:31:03.750 --> 01:31:07.337
I actually still have
the prayer in my wallet, um...

01:31:07.463 --> 01:31:09.089
I usually don't read prayers,
but I will.

01:31:09.214 --> 01:31:11.049
I mean, I do, but not for...

01:31:11.717 --> 01:31:12.759
All right.

01:31:13.552 --> 01:31:16.180
"Dear Lord, as I stumble
through this life,"

01:31:16.305 --> 01:31:18.515
"help me to create more laughter
than tears,"

01:31:18.640 --> 01:31:20.476
"dispense more happiness
than gloom,"

01:31:20.601 --> 01:31:22.769
"spread more cheer
than despair."

